'''''California''''' (663 tons) is the most famous of four [[Dutch clipper]]s launched in 1853. An iron-[[Hull (watercraft)|hull]]ed [[Clipper ship|clipper]], she was built by [[Fop Smit]] and mastered by F.C. Jaski for the company L. Bienfait & sn. On the maiden voyage Jaski sailed her in 86 days from [[The Downs (ship anchorage)|The Downs]] to [[Port Adelaide]], delivering a hundred English immigrants.
