{{Politics of Comoros}}

'''Dialogue Proposition Action''' (DPA-Mwangaza) was a political party in the [[Comoros]] led by [[Mohamed Saïd Abdallah Mchangama]].

==History==
The party received 5.4% of the vote in the [[Comorian legislative election, 1992|1992 elections]], winning seats in the [[Assembly of the Union of the Comoros|Assembly of the Union]].<ref>[https://www.africaintelligence.com/ION/politics/1992/12/05/no-legislative-majority,17598-ART?CXT=CANP&country=COMOROS%20ISLANDS Comoros Islands: No legislative majority]{{dead link|date=December 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} African Intelligence, 5 December 1992</ref>

In October 1993 it merged into the [[Rally for Democracy and Renewal]],<ref>[http://www.ipu.org/parline-e/reports/arc/2069_93.htm Elections held in 1993] IPU</ref><ref>Tom Lansford (2015) ''Political Handbook of the World 2015'', CQ Press</ref> which went on to win the [[Comorian legislative election, 1993|parliamentary elections]] in December.

