{{Infobox language |name = Kitara |nativename = ''Runyakitara'' |created = early 1990s |creator = [[Uganda]] |speakers = Written language taught at university. 5 million speakers of the source languages |date = 2002 |ref = <ref>{{e18}}</ref> |family = [[standard language]] |posteriori = [[Kiga language|Kiga]], [[Nkore language|Nkore]], [[Nyoro language|Nyoro]], & [[Tooro language|Tooro]] |glotto=none |guthrie = JE.10A }}
The '''Kitara language''', commonly known as '''''Runyakitara''''', is an artificial<ref name="Guthrie"/> [[standard language]] based on four closely related languages of western [[Uganda]]: *[[Nyoro language|Nyoro or ''Runyoro'']] *[[Kiga language|Kiga (Chiga) or ''Rukiga'']] *[[Nkore language|Nkore or ''Runyankole'']] *[[Tooro language|Tooro or ''Rutooro'']]
The Google interface has been translated into Kitara in February 2010 by the Faculty of Computing and IT, Makerere University.
