[[File:Nanuk Míša (6).JPG|thumb|Míša]]
'''Míša''' is a popular [[Czech Republic|Czech]] brand of frozen confection. Míšas have been made continuously since 1961, and sell over 12 million ice pops per year, making it the most successful [[ice cream]] brand in the Czech Republic. It has survived events such as the [[Velvet Revolution]] and is fondly remembered as an integral part of Czech childhood.<ref name="unilever.cz">{{cite web|title=MÍŠA|url=http://www.unilever.cz/our-brands/detail/misa/309234//|website=Unilever.cz|accessdate=2014-10-03}}</ref>

They are made with frozen quark, rather than ice cream or yogurt.<ref name="unilever.cz"/>

The [[logo]] features a grinning green [[bear]] as the brand's mascot, holding its [[arm]]s above the word "Míša."<ref name="unilever.cz"/>

